# @ver0/eslint-config Stack Overview

## Core Technologies

- **Node.js** - Runtime environment
- **ESLint v9** - Core linting engine
- **TypeScript** - Static type checking support
- **Prettier** - Code formatting

## ESLint Plugins

- **@eslint/js** - JavaScript core rules
- **@eslint/json** - JSON file linting
- **@eslint/markdown** - Markdown file linting
- **@vitest/eslint-plugin** - Vitest testing rules
- **eslint-plugin-import** - Import/export validation
- **eslint-plugin-n** - Node.js specific rules
- **eslint-plugin-react** - React specific rules
- **eslint-plugin-unicorn** - Additional helpful rules
- **eslint-plugin-promise** - Promise-related best practices
- **eslint-plugin-prettier** - Prettier integration
- **typescript-eslint** - TypeScript support

## Presets & Configurations

- **eslint-config-xo** - Base XO ruleset
- **eslint-config-xo-react** - XO React rules
- **eslint-config-xo-typescript** - XO TypeScript rules
- **eslint-config-prettier** - Disables ESLint rules conflicting with Prettier

## Development Tools

- **semantic-release** - Automated versioning and publishing
- **commitlint** - Enforces semantic commit messages
- **husky** - Git hooks for process automation
- **lint-staged** - Runs linters on staged files
- **@ver0/eslint-formatter-gha** - GitHub Actions formatted output

## Module System

- Uses ES Modules (`"type": "module"` in package.json)
- Exports configuration builder functions
- Leverages modern JavaScript features

## Versioning & Publishing

- Published on npm as `@ver0/eslint-config`
- MIT License
- Public access configured in publishConfig 